&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**THIS VACANCY IS ONLY OPEN TO EMPLOYEES OF WORCESTERSHIRE ACUTE HOSPITALS NHS TRUST**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering an exciting opportunity to join our Professional Development Team within the Emergency Department. The post-holder will contribute to the provision of high quality education, training and development opportunities to our team. You will be expected to use highly developed interpersonal and communication skills in order to develop support and motivate individuals and groups within the learning environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role will suit an enthusiastic, highly motivated and adaptable professional who is passionate about the Clinical Education and Professional Practice Standards of Nurses, Healthcare Support Workers and International Nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is fundamental to providing assurance of standards and enabling continuing personal, professional and practice development as an integral part of the acute nursing philosophy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate should be:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A registered healthcare professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educated to/demonstrating an ability to work at degree level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A teaching qualification e.g. mentorship or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of planning and delivering educational activities and staff development within an acute health care setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Above all you will have an enthusiasm and passion for teaching and developing staff and the ability to work in partnership with all stakeholders to fulfil the needs of the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information about this role please contact Jonathan Dickens on 01905 733122.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
